\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 Concerns \b \i0 \ul0 [**26]\b0 \i0 \ul0   that S.B. 1070 will adversely impact the ability of Latino children to obtain an education are well founded. One Arizona school district voted to oppose S.B. 1070 in court because of concerns about its ability to comply with \b0 \i \ul0 Plyler v. Doe\b0 \i0 \ul0  in light of the unconstitutional provisions of S.B. 1070. n18 And the United States Department of Justice together with the United States Department of Education took the unusual step of jointly providing nationwide guidance to schools and local officials after becoming "aware of student enrollment practices that may chill or discourage the participation, or lead to the exclusion, of students based on their or their parents' or guardians'  \b \i0 \ul0 [*14]\b0 \i0 \ul0   actual or perceived citizenship or immigration status." n19
