\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 The preliminary injunction appears to have alleviated some of the expected decline in enrollment. For example, the Mesa School District expected to see a drop of over 2,000 students due in large part to S.B. 1070. n20 After the injunction issued, however, the district lost only a few hundred students. n21 If the Enjoined Provisions are allowed to take effect, school districts will likely face a precipitous additional decline in enrollment as Latinos who took a wait-and-see attitude flee Arizona or pull their children from school for the reasons outlined above. n22
