\par \fs16 \pard \ql \li600\ri0 \sb0 \fi0 n50 The 287(g) program currently requires local law enforcement to receive four weeks of training from Immigration and Customs Enforcement officers on immigration law and procedures. The U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement Academy sets standards and testing for the program, as well. See U.S. Dep't of Homeland Security, Fact Sheet: Delegation of Immigration Authority Section 287(g) Immigration and Nationality Act (2010), http://www.ice.gov/news/library/factsheets/287g.htm.
